text.tspan: Share of children vaccinated against measles vs. against diphtheria, tetanus, and pertussis,
Shown is the second-dose measles vaccination coverage of children against the DTP3 vaccination coverage of 12 to 23 month old children. The age at
which children receive the second vaccination of measles varies between countries but is typically between 15 months and 6 years old.
Data source: WHO, Global Health Observatory
